verses.verse: A Psalm<WH4210> of David<WH1732>. The earth<WH776> is the LORD'S<WH3068>, and the fulness<WH4393> thereof; the world<WH8398>, and they that dwell<WH3427> therein.
For he hath founded<WH3245> it upon the seas<WH3220>, and established<WH3559> it upon the floods<WH5104>.
Who shall ascend<WH5927> into the hill<WH2022> of the LORD<WH3068>? or who shall stand<WH6965> in his holy<WH6944> place<WH4725>?

He that hath clean<WH5355> hands<WH3709>, and a pure<WH1249> heart<WH3824>; who hath not lifted up<WH5375> his soul<WH5315> unto vanity<WH7723>, nor sworn<WH7650> deceitfully<WH4820>. He: Heb. The clean of hands
He shall receive<WH5375> the blessing<WH1293> from the LORD<WH3068>, and righteousness<WH6666> from the God<WH430> of his salvation<WH3468>.
This is the generation<WH1755> of them that seek<WH1875> him, that seek<WH1245> thy face<WH6440>, O Jacob<WH3290>. Selah<WH5542>. O Jacob: or, O God of Jacob
Lift up<WH5375> your heads<WH7218>, O ye gates<WH8179>; and be ye lift up<WH5375>, ye everlasting<WH5769> doors<WH6607>; and the King<WH4428> of glory<WH3519> shall come in<WH935>.
Who is this King<WH4428> of glory<WH3519>? The LORD<WH3068> strong<WH5808> and mighty<WH1368>, the LORD<WH3068> mighty<WH1368> in battle<WH4421>.
Lift up<WH5375> your heads<WH7218>, O ye gates<WH8179>; even lift them up<WH5375>, ye everlasting<WH5769> doors<WH6607>; and the King<WH4428> of glory<WH3519> shall come in<WH935>.
Who is this King<WH4428> of glory<WH3519>? The LORD<WH3068> of hosts<WH6635>, he is the King<WH4428> of glory<WH3519>. Selah<WH5542>.
